{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"S2 implementation complete (offline verified: make lint + mypy + 45 review_bot tests all green). Summary:\n- gerrit_client.py: get_commit, get_merge_files (no-parent auto-merge map), get_file_diff (per-file no-parent), get_mergelist + MAGIC_PATHS. Never bare /patch on merges.\n- voter.py: merge detection (get_commit parents>=2) INSIDE review_and_vote AFTER the existing-vote check, BEFORE any diff fetch — so webhook + backfill + /rerun all route through it (reconcile.py unchanged, proven by test_voter_merge_detection_via_backfill_path). _assemble_merge_diff fetches files/mergelist + per-file diffs until DIFF_CHAR_CAP; ANY merge-path REST failure re-raises -> fail-closed -1. MERGE_CHANGE_ERROR stderr marker (+ merge metric) AND the outer VOTER_ERROR (double-signal).\n- assemble.py: assemble_merge_change_context(merge_files, file_diffs, mergelist) — ## Merge context (mergelist, MERGELIST_MAX_COMMITS=100 count-cap + truncation notice) then ## Auto-merge diff (real files only; empty-diff clean-merge notice); combined DIFF_CHAR_CAP apportionment (context first, diff truncated last).\n- adapter.py: merge_commits threaded through code_review_decision -> _message_tag WITHOUT breaking the strict _TAG_SUFFIXES lookup -> tag '[LLM-Review: PASS (merge-change, N integrated commit(s))]'.\n- Fixtures: tests/fixtures/review_bot_merge/ LIVE-captured from Gerrit 3.14.1 change 183 (files no-parent => {/COMMIT_MSG,/MERGE_LIST} for a clean merge, proving files/ returns the auto-merge base map NOT a 409). Citing test + README cite rest-api-changes.html#list-files.\n- 15 new tests: fixture endpoint proof, assemble format/empty/count-cap/char-cap, merge vote+tag, never-get_patch (409 guard), empty-diff review, parametrized fail-closed for all 4 REST methods, backfill routing, /rerun force routing, render_diff_info.\n- Observability: observability.sh section 4c (MERGE_CHANGE_ERROR -> review_bot_merge_change_errors) + monitoring_88ab.tf alarm WITH SNS action (terraform fmt clean).\nLive smoke (merge change 195 receives a vote w/ merge tag) in progress."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783058762724768001,"uuid":"5625c2e7-face-40c8-a37d-e9f1c8628928"}